    "causal_summary": "The current `RecursiveSplitter` (indexer.py:33-39, defaults chunk_size=1500, overlap=200, min=250) produces chunks by line-window, ignoring code structure. For `structural-indexer.ts` (2,234 lines, 67 chunks), the chunk that surfaces at dense rank 1 for the probe \"filesystem walker that emits typed structural symbols and import edges\" is **chunk 44683 = lines 1-9** — the import header — not the `findFiles` function (1391-1465) or the class body (anywhere). The reranker is starved of content.",
